set -ex

# Execute this script on macOS, from the repo's root, to run the whole codegen pipeline associated with the SpeziHealthKit package:

# 1: run the gyb, to generate the SampleType definitions (and some input sources for the Codegen)
#    you need to have the [`gyb`](https://github.com/swiftlang/swift/blob/main/utils/gyb.py) script in your for this step.
./useGYB

# 2: run the localization processing step, to populate the strings catalogues in the various lproj folders in
#    SpeziHealthKit's Resources folder.
swift run LocalizationsProcessor -o Sources/SpeziHealthKit/Resources/ en de en_GB es es_US fr

# 3: run the linux sample types codegen step. this depends on sources generated by the gyb step, and therefore is at the end.
swift run Codegen -o Sources/SpeziHealthKit/Sample\ Types/Linux/HKTypeIdentifiers+Linux.swift
